VC. SURESH KUMARRaga Sudha recently celebrated its 35th Thyagaraja Aradhana  at the  Kala Subba Rao mini theatre.The function started with the recitation ofVishnu Sahsranamamby a group of ladies from Nallakunta Shirdi Sai Samajam, led by  Sundari. This was followed byGuru Vandanamby the students of Raga Sudha, who sang devotional songs tuned and composed by  Indiramani. Subsequently, C. Indiramani led the group for thePanchratna Kritisof Thaygayya and was supported by  Padmaja, Sangeeta, Aruna and other students of Raga Sudha.The songs were rendered by the group without referring to the script or book and were well-received by the audience. Giving them company was Narayana on the violin and Kapa Srinivasa Rao on the mridangam. The programme ended with a tableau scripted and directed by  Indiramani, titled Jagam Sangeetamayam. The tableau depicted the saints Thyagayya, purandradasa, Muthuswamy Dikshitar and Annamaya imagining the scenes for their songs penned by them. The scene depicting the wedding of Lord Rama with Sita was the highlight and received thunderous applause from the gathering.The participating students were  Sai Revathi as Ganesa, Hamsika as Subramanyawsamy, Prakhya as Siva, Likita as Bageerata, Sneha as Viswamitra, Meghana as Vamana, Deepti as Krishna, Sruti as Rama, Kruthi as Lakshamana, Sreenija as Seeta, Vishala as Hanuman, A.Deepti as Annamaya, Atiti as Purandaradas, Ragna as Deekshitar, Sreenija as Thyagaya and Abhisekh as Venkateswara. Chandrasekhar did the compeering, while C. Subramaniam did the overall supervision.The chief guest for the function was Madhusudhan Rao, Director, Doordarshan, Hyderabad.Bottom Template Starts
